ategory:Sportspeople from Portland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Olympic track and field athletes of the United States]]\n[[Category:Oregon Ducks men's track and field athletes]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cuban emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:American people of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:People from Wayland, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:American track and field coaches]]\n[[Category:New York City Marathon male winners]]\n[[Category:Boston Marathon male winners]]\n[[Category:Congressional Gold Medal recipients]]\n[[Category:Sports coaches from Oregon]]\n[[Category:Oregon Ducks men's cross country runners]]\n", "name_user": "KazimierzSiemienowicz", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCollegiate", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alberto_Salazar"}
{"title_page": "Demographics of Yukon", "text_new": "'''[[Yukon]]''' is the westernmost of [[Canada|Canada's]] three northern [[Territories of Canada|territories]]. Its capital is [[Whitehorse, Yukon|Whitehorse]]. People from Yukon are known as ''Yukoners'' ({{lang-fr|Yukonnais}}).\n\nPopulation of Yukon: 35,874 ([[Canada 2016 Census|2016]])<ref name=\"2016census\">{{cite web | url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/hlt-fst/pd-pl/Table.cfm?Lang=Eng&T=101&S=50&O=A | title=Population and dwelling counts, for Canada, provinces and territories, 2016 and 2011 censuses | work=[[Statistics Canada]] | date=February 2, 2017 | accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\nPercentage of Canadian population : 0.10%\n\nPopulation growth rate for 2007: +5.8%\n\n==Population of Yukon since 1901==\n{{Graph:Chart\n | width = 950\n | height= 450\n | type = line\n | interpolate = \n | xType = date\n | xAxisAngle = \n | yAxisTitle = Population\n | yGrid = yes\n | linewidth = 2\n | x =1901, 1911, 1921, 1931, 1941, 1951, 1956, 1961, 1966, 1971, 1975, 1981, 1986, 1991, 1996, 2001, 2006, 2011, 2016\n | y = 27219, 8512, 4157, 4230, 4914, 9096, 12190, 14628, 14382, 18390, 21835, 23150, 23505, 27797, 30766, 28674, 30372, 33897, 35874\n | colors = #fcc917\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Population\n!Five-year<br/>% change\n!Ten-year<br/>% change\n!Rank among provinces<br />and territories\n|-\n|1901 ||27,219 ||n/a ||n/a ||10\n|-\n|1911 ||8,512 ||n/a ||-68.7 ||10\n|-\n|1921 ||4,157 ||n/a ||-51.1 ||10\n|-\n|1931 ||4,230 ||n/a ||1.8 ||11\n|-\n|1941 ||4,914 ||n/a ||16.2 ||11\n|-\n|1951 ||9,096 ||n/a ||85.1 ||12\n|-\n|1956 ||12,190 ||34.0 ||n/a ||12\n|-\n|1961 ||14,628 ||20.0 ||60.8 ||12\n|-\n|1966 ||14,382 ||-1.7 ||18.0 ||12\n|-\n|1971 ||18,390 ||27.9 ||25.7 ||12\n|-\n|1976 ||21,835 ||18.7 ||51.8 ||12\n|-\n|1981 ||23,150 ||6.0 ||25.9 ||12\n|-\n|1986 ||23,505 ||1.5 ||7.6 ||12\n|-\n|1991 ||27,797 ||18.3 ||20.1 ||12\n|-\n|1996 ||30,766 ||10.7 ||30.9 ||12\n|-\n|2001 ||28,674 ||-6.8 |